{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "MixingRatio",
        "description": "Volume (mole) mixing ratio of an atmospheric species: xi = c_i / c_total, the ratio of the species molar concentration to the total molar concentration of air. Migrated from AtmosphericDynamics.jl@816cc391 src/seinfeld_pandis_ch1.jl:278 (`MixingRatio` @component). Implements Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) Chapter 1 Equation 1.6. The mixing ratio is dimensionless (stored with unit 1) and in the atmosphere spans roughly twelve orders of magnitude — from ~0.78 for the dominant gas N2 down to parts-per-trillion (~1e-12) trace species — so it is conventionally quoted in ppm, ppb, or ppt. Parameterized as observed-only: c_i and c_total are inputs (parameters in standalone form), xi is the algebraic output. Upstream the Julia @component declares c_i, c_total, and xi as @variables for composition into a parent system; for standalone serialization (3 unknowns vs 1 equation otherwise) c_i and c_total are declared as parameters here, mirroring the IdealGasLaw / ScaleHeight / RelativeHumidity serialization pattern in this directory.",
        "tags": [
            "atmospheric_dynamics",
            "seinfeld-pandis",
            "observed-only",
            "ch1",
            "mixing-ratio"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "AtmosphericDynamics.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-xvn9)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Seinfeld, J. H., & Pandis, S. N. (2006). Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics: From Air Pollution to Climate Change, 2nd ed. Wiley. Chapter 1, Eq. 1.6 (volume mixing ratio, xi_i = c_i / c_total). ISBN 978-0-471-72018-8."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "MixingRatio": {
            "reference": {
                "notes": "source_ref: AtmosphericDynamics.jl@816cc391:src/seinfeld_pandis_ch1.jl:278\nUpstream `MixingRatio` is an MTK `@component` with c_i(t), c_total(t), and xi(t) as `@variables` and the single equation xi ~ c_i / c_total (Seinfeld & Pandis Eq. 1.6). For standalone serialization — and to make the component well-posed in isolation (3 unknowns against 1 equation otherwise) — c_i and c_total are declared as parameters here, with xi the single algebraic state. This matches the bead's `(S, observed-only)` classification in docs/migration-tracker.md and the IdealGasLaw / ScaleHeight / RelativeHumidity serialization pattern in this directory. The upstream `5.5 MixingRatio Compilation` test (test/seinfeld_pandis_ch1_test.jl:485) confirms this input/output split: it compiles the component with `inputs = [mr_nns.c_i, mr_nns.c_total]`, leaving xi as the sole computed unknown. The single algebraic equation is unchanged from upstream.\n\nUpstream provides only structural (`1.5 MixingRatio Structure`) and compilation (`5.5 MixingRatio Compilation`) tests for this component — no numerical-accuracy test. The inline `tests` here therefore anchor on textbook reference values: the total molar concentrations 40.9 mol/m^3 (T = 298 K, p = 101325 Pa) and 44.6 mol/m^3 (STP, T = 273.15 K) given in the chapter's TotalMolarConcentration discussion, and the standard dry-air mole fractions (N2 0.7808, O2 0.2095, Ar 0.0093, CO2 ~4e-4). Each test's c_i is c_i = X * c_total for the named mole fraction X, so xi reproduces X.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-6): observed-only single-equation algebraic system (no ODE integration); 1e-6 covers float64 roundoff in the single c_i / c_total divide across the full atmospheric mixing-ratio range — xi from 1 (a pure species, c_i = c_total) down to ~1e-12 (parts-per-trillion trace species)."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1.0e-6
            },
            "variables": {
                "c_i": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "mol/m^3",
                    "default": 0.01636,
                    "description": "Molar concentration of species i. Default 0.01636 mol/m^3 — a CO2-like trace species at a ~400 ppm mixing ratio in air at 298 K, 1 atm (c_i = 4e-4 * c_total)."
                },
                "c_total": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "mol/m^3",
                    "default": 40.9,
                    "description": "Total molar concentration of air. Default 40.9 mol/m^3 — the value at T = 298 K, p = 101325 Pa from the ideal-gas law c_total = p / (R * T) (Seinfeld & Pandis Ch 1; 44.6 mol/m^3 at STP)."
                },
                "xi": {
                    "type": "state",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Volume (mole) mixing ratio of species i, dimensionless — the fraction c_i / c_total. Conventionally quoted in ppm, ppb, or ppt."
                }
            },
            "equations": [
                {
                    "_comment": "Eq. 1.6 - Volume mixing ratio definition: xi = c_i / c_total",
                    "lhs": "xi",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": ["c_i", "c_total"]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "co2_400ppm_default",
                    "description": "Canonical default-parameter run: a CO2-like trace species at a ~400 ppm mixing ratio in air at 298 K, 1 atm (c_i = 0.01636 mol/m^3 = 4e-4 * c_total, c_total = 40.9 mol/m^3). Verifies the defining ratio xi = c_i / c_total of Eq. 1.6. The system is algebraic (xi depends only on the input parameters), so xi is also asserted at t = 1.0 to confirm time-invariance.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "c_i": 0.01636,
                        "c_total": 40.9
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "xi", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0004 },
                        { "variable": "xi", "time": 1.0, "expected": 0.0004 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "nitrogen_dominant",
                    "description": "Dominant atmospheric gas: molecular nitrogen at its standard dry-air mole fraction 0.7808 (c_i = 31.93472 mol/m^3 = 0.7808 * c_total, c_total = 40.9 mol/m^3). Exercises the high end of the mixing-ratio range — N2 makes up roughly four-fifths of dry air.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "c_i": 31.93472,
                        "c_total": 40.9
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "xi", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.7808 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "oxygen_major",
                    "description": "Second most abundant gas: molecular oxygen at its standard dry-air mole fraction 0.2095 (c_i = 8.56855 mol/m^3 = 0.2095 * c_total, c_total = 40.9 mol/m^3). With nitrogen_dominant this confirms the two major air components; the expected value carries the float64 round-off of the divide.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "c_i": 8.56855,
                        "c_total": 40.9
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "xi", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.20950000000000002 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "argon_minor",
                    "description": "Argon, the third most abundant atmospheric gas, at its standard dry-air mole fraction 0.0093 (c_i = 0.38037 mol/m^3 = 0.0093 * c_total, c_total = 40.9 mol/m^3). A sub-percent minor constituent — bridges the major gases and the trace species.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "c_i": 0.38037,
                        "c_total": 40.9
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "xi", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0093 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "ozone_trace_ppb",
                    "description": "Trace pollutant regime: ozone at a boundary-layer mole fraction of 50 ppb (c_i = 2.045e-6 mol/m^3 = 5e-8 * c_total, c_total = 40.9 mol/m^3). Exercises the parts-per-billion end of the range, where mixing ratios are conventionally quoted in ppb.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "c_i": 2.045e-6,
                        "c_total": 40.9
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "xi", "time": 0.0, "expected": 5.0e-8 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "stp_total_concentration",
                    "description": "Different total-concentration regime: a 1% mixing ratio evaluated at the STP total molar concentration c_total = 44.6 mol/m^3 (T = 273.15 K, p = 101325 Pa) rather than the 298 K value 40.9 mol/m^3. c_i = 0.446 mol/m^3 = 0.01 * c_total. Confirms xi is set by the ratio, independent of the absolute concentration scale.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "c_i": 0.446,
                        "c_total": 44.6
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "xi", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.01 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "pure_species",
                    "description": "Upper-boundary case: the species fills the entire air sample (c_i = c_total = 40.9 mol/m^3), giving the maximum physical mixing ratio xi = 1. xi is algebraic, so the value is also asserted at t = 1.0 to confirm time-invariance.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "c_i": 40.9,
                        "c_total": 40.9
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "xi", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0 },
                        { "variable": "xi", "time": 1.0, "expected": 1.0 }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "ultratrace_ppt",
                    "description": "Extreme low end: an ultra-trace species at a parts-per-trillion mole fraction ~1e-12 (c_i = 4.09e-11 mol/m^3 = 1e-12 * c_total, c_total = 40.9 mol/m^3). Exercises the bottom of the ~12-order-of-magnitude atmospheric mixing-ratio span; the expected value carries the float64 round-off of the divide.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "c_i": 4.09e-11,
                        "c_total": 40.9
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
                        { "variable": "xi", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0000000000000002e-12 }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "xi_vs_species_concentration",
                    "description": "Volume mixing ratio as a function of the species molar concentration at a fixed total molar concentration (c_total = 40.9 mol/m^3, air at 298 K, 1 atm). Reproduces the linear definition xi = c_i / c_total of Eq. 1.6: c_i is swept from 0 to c_total, so xi covers its full physical range 0 to 1.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "c_total": 40.9
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "c_i",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 40.9, "count": 25, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "xi_vs_ci",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Volume mixing ratio xi as a function of species molar concentration at c_total = 40.9 mol/m^3.",
                            "x": { "variable": "c_i", "label": "Species molar concentration (mol/m^3)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "xi",  "label": "Volume mixing ratio (dimensionless)" }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "xi_vs_total_concentration",
                    "description": "Volume mixing ratio as a function of the total molar concentration of air at a fixed species concentration (c_i = 0.01636 mol/m^3, a CO2-like trace amount). Reproduces the inverse xi proportional-to 1/c_total dependence: at fixed species content, denser air (larger c_total) dilutes the species to a smaller mixing ratio. c_total is swept from 20 mol/m^3 (mid-troposphere) to 45 mol/m^3 (cold, dense surface air).",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {
                        "c_i": 0.01636
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "c_total",
                                "range": { "start": 20.0, "stop": 45.0, "count": 25, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "xi_vs_ctotal",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Volume mixing ratio xi as a function of total air molar concentration at c_i = 0.01636 mol/m^3.",
                            "x": { "variable": "c_total", "label": "Total molar concentration of air (mol/m^3)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "xi",      "label": "Volume mixing ratio (dimensionless)" }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "xi_concentration_heatmap",
                    "description": "Two-dimensional sweep over species concentration and total air concentration. Surfaces the full xi = c_i / c_total response: the mixing ratio rises with c_i and falls with c_total. c_i is swept from 0 to 20 mol/m^3 and c_total from 20 to 45 mol/m^3, so c_i <= c_total throughout and xi stays within its physical range 0 to 1.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {},
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "c_i",
                                "range": { "start": 0.0, "stop": 20.0, "count": 12, "scale": "linear" }
                            },
                            {
                                "parameter": "c_total",
                                "range": { "start": 20.0, "stop": 45.0, "count": 12, "scale": "linear" }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "xi_heatmap",
                            "type": "heatmap",
                            "description": "Volume mixing ratio xi as a function of species molar concentration and total air molar concentration.",
                            "x": { "variable": "c_i",     "label": "Species molar concentration (mol/m^3)" },
                            "y": { "variable": "c_total", "label": "Total molar concentration of air (mol/m^3)" },
                            "value": { "variable": "xi", "reduce": "final" }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
